NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Next, let us discuss dee's cue bid. Many people play that you can cue bid with either 3 or 4 card support. I personally like it to show 4 card support. I think the difference between an 8 and 9 card fit is huge. So, I would bid 2D with dee's hand, but many would bid 3C. It is just a matter of whether a cue bid guarantees four-card support or three. Some people play a "mixed raise" convention. Where 2N shows 3 card support, 3C shows 4 card support.|
